sentences: Shin Ji-min (Korean: 신지민; born January 8, 1991), better known mononymously as Jimin, is a South Korean former rapper and singer.
She was the leader and main rapper of the girl group AOA, which debuted in 2012 under FNC Entertainment.
In 2015, Jimin was a semi-finalist in the first season of Unpretty Rapstar.
Following allegations of bullying by former bandmate Kwon Mina, Jimin left the group and retired from the entertainment industry in July 2020.
Jimin was born on January 8, 1991, in Seongnam, Gyeonggi, South Korea.
